Why this file exists
--------------------
macOS 15+ (Sequoia, Tahoe/26) blocks NFS access for every process spawned
by launchd or cron, regardless of UID. LaunchDaemons on this host
(com.hermes.agent, com.acatome.extract-watch, …) and cron jobs
(daily_briefing, quest runner, sortie-runner) cannot touch /opt/shared
until each interpreter has been granted Full Disk Access.

Apple removed the `profiles install` CLI in macOS 26 and now requires
PPPC/FDA profiles to come from an approved MDM server. For a small
cluster we skip MDM entirely and grant FDA manually in System Settings.
This is a one-time chore per host.

How to grant (once per host)
----------------------------

 1. Screen-share or log in locally to {{ inventory_hostname }}
    (physical console, VNC, or Tailscale Screen Sharing).

 2. Open **System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access**.

 3. Click the **"+"** button at the bottom of the list. Authenticate
    with an admin password when prompted.

 4. In the file picker press **Cmd + Shift + G** to reveal the path
    entry field. Paste a path from the list below, press **Return**,
    then click **Open**.

 5. Repeat step 4 for every binary listed below.

 6. Double-check that the toggle next to each new entry is **ON (blue)**.

 7. Restart the daemons so they re-exec under the fresh grant:
      launchctl kickstart -k system/com.hermes.agent
      launchctl kickstart -k system/com.acatome.extract-watch

