How stable are these grants?
----------------------------

All venv pythons on this host are **symlinks** to Homebrew-installed
Python frameworks under /opt/homebrew/opt/python@*. macOS FDA records
the *resolved* binary's cdhash, so:

  - `uv pip install` / Ansible re-runs inside the venv   → grant stable
  - `brew upgrade python@3.12` / `python@3.14`           → grant BREAKS,
    re-add the affected venv python (this file regenerates on each
    Ansible run so you can re-open it to see the current set).
  - macOS major version upgrade                           → Apple re-signs
    /usr/sbin/cron etc. with the same identity → grant stable.

If you want to avoid the brew-upgrade breakage entirely, pin the
Python formulas:
      brew pin python@3.14
      brew pin python@3.12

Verifying grants are live
-------------------------

    sudo sqlite3 "/Library/Application Support/com.apple.TCC/TCC.db" \
      "SELECT client, auth_value FROM access \
       WHERE service='kTCCServiceSystemPolicyAllFiles';"

`auth_value = 2` means granted. Re-run this after clicking through the
list above — you should see one row per entry.
